result.execSummary:
The defendant Angela Flowers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
CONDITIONS AS TO ALL COUNTS:
Batterers Intervention program. Parenting classes. Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment. Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.

No contact with victims David N. or M.R.W., unless approved by agent or court, after approval only contact with M.R.W. if desired by M.R.W. State and defense agree to no violent contact between defendant and victims if approved by agent or court. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.

Pay all Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Court WAIVED all NON-mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges.

No contact with firearms. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

Defendant Angela Flowers in court with attorney Jeffrey A Schwarz.  Cynthia M Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
AS TO COUNTS 1, 2 & 3 of the AMENDED INFORMATION
Defendant changes plea(s) to NO CONTEST. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence. Case adjourned to branch 23 for Sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 18, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
